In addition, engineering and administrative controls are implemented to reduce the chance of an accidental release to the environment.  The cylinders are equipped with a fusible relief plug which protects the equipment from overpressurization and rupture.  The cylinders are inspected upon delivery, and any cylinders with damage are rejected and returned to the supplier.  All cylinder maintenance is performed by the chemical supply vendor.



The fill process is located inside the production building. The building ventilation fan and neutralization tank/scrubber system are turned on prior to operating the process.  Any vapors produced during fill is exhausted through the ventilation fan and discharged to the neutralization tank/scrubber system located outside the building.   Sensors are also installed in the production building and the scrubber exhaust to monitor releases of sulfur dioxide.



There are check valves on the fill line from the sulfur dioxide cylinder to the sulfurous acid container to prevent contamination of the sulfur dioxide. In addition, there are safety relief valves in the fill process.  If a relief valve actuates during fill, any sulfur dioxide vapor would be exhausted through the ventilation fan and discharged to the neutralization tank/scrubber system.



